{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.38",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 38,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 38",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 38 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:1",
      "text": "Then Yahweh answered Job out of the whirlwind,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:2",
      "text": "“ Who is this who darkens counsel by words without knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:3",
      "text": "Brace yourself like a man, for I will question you, then you answer me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:4",
      "text": "“Where were you when I laid the foundations of the earth? Declare, if you have understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:5",
      "text": "Who determined its measures, if you know? Or who stretched the line on it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:6",
      "text": "What were its foundations fastened on? Or who laid its cornerstone,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:7",
      "text": "when the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:8",
      "text": "“ Or who shut up the sea with doors, when it broke out of the womb,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:9",
      "text": "when I made clouds its garment, and wrapped it in thick darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:10",
      "text": "marked out for it my bound, set bars and doors,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:11",
      "text": "and said, ‘ You may come here, but no further. Your proud waves shall be stopped here ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:12",
      "text": "“ Have you commanded the morning in your days, and caused the dawn to know its place,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:13",
      "text": "that it might take hold of the ends of the earth, and shake the wicked out of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:14",
      "text": "It is changed as clay under the seal, and presented as a garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:15",
      "text": "From the wicked, their light is withheld. The high arm is broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:16",
      "text": "“ Have you entered into the springs of the sea? Or have you walked in the recesses of the deep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:17",
      "text": "Have the gates of death been revealed to you? Or have you seen the gates of the shadow of death?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:18",
      "text": "Have you comprehended the earth in its width? Declare, if you know it all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:19",
      "text": "“ What is the way to the dwelling of light? As for darkness, where is its place,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:20",
      "text": "that you should take it to its bound, that you should discern the paths to its house?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:21",
      "text": "Surely you know, for you were born then, and the number of your days is great!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:22",
      "text": "Have you entered the storehouses of the snow, or have you seen the storehouses of the hail,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:23",
      "text": "which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:24",
      "text": "By what way is the lightning distributed, or the east wind scattered on the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:25",
      "text": "Who has cut a channel for the flood water, or the path for the thunderstorm,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:26",
      "text": "to cause it to rain on a land where there is no man, on the wilderness, in which there is no man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:27",
      "text": "to satisfy the waste and desolate ground, to cause the tender grass to grow?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:28",
      "text": "Does the rain have a father? Or who fathers the drops of dew?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:29",
      "text": "Whose womb did the ice come out of? Who has given birth to the gray frost of the sky?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:30",
      "text": "The waters become hard like stone, when the surface of the deep is frozen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:31",
      "text": "“Can you bind the cluster of the Pleiades, or loosen the cords of Orion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:32",
      "text": "Can you lead the constellations out in their season? Or can you guide the Bear with her cubs?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:33",
      "text": "Do you know the laws of the heavens? Can you establish its dominion over the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:34",
      "text": "“Can you lift up your voice to the clouds, that abundance of waters may cover you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:35",
      "text": "Can you send out lightnings, that they may go? Do they report to you, ‘ Here we are’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:36",
      "text": "Who has put wisdom in the inward parts? Or who has given understanding to the mind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:37",
      "text": "Who can count the clouds by wisdom? Or who can pour out the containers of the sky,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:38",
      "text": "when the dust runs into a mass, and the clods of earth stick together?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:39",
      "text": "“Can you hunt the prey for the lioness, or satisfy the appetite of the young lions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:40",
      "text": "when they crouch in their dens, and lie in wait in the thicket?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.38.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:41",
      "text": "Who provides for the raven his prey, when his young ones cry to God, and wander for lack of food?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
